Description: A sealing for an unknown object, probably a document: one complete oval impression from an intaglio gem and parts of three others. The main stamp has a human figure, probably a female deity, facing a royal cobra, both on the same plinth. One of the other impressions is the same, the other two are different but very incomplete. Unfired pale yellow-brown mud.
Curator's comments: Terracotta IV Donated: Egypt Exploration Society. Roman, probably second century AD.
Bibliographic references: Terracotta / Catalogue of Terracottas in the British Museum (3640)
